parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle sticking or cruise control cable can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates without pressing the gas pedal
the cruise control cable becomes detached and jams
and the vehicle may not respond to braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience sudden loss of power
or unusual noises while driving. The transmission may also slip or hesitate
causing the vehicle to jerk or vibrate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the torque converter can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience sudden loss of power
or unusual noises while driving. The transmission may also slip or hesitate
causing the vehicle to jerk or vibrate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake light switch can cause the vehicle's gearshift to become stuck in park, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle's gearshift may become stuck in park
or the brake lights may remain illuminated even when the brake pedal is not depressed.
